 in print and visual media, inspired late seventeenth-century Jesuits from German-speaking lands to bring Catholicism and European gender norms to the Spanish-controlled Pacific. As Strasser demonstrates, the age of global missions hinged on the reproduction of missionary manhood in print and real life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 4aAUP Wetenschappelijk. 4aEarly Modern Period. 4aGender Studies. 4aHistory. 4aSociology and Social History. 4aTheology and Religion. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 17th Century.2bisacsh  aEarly modern masculinities, gender, missions, Jesuits, German.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311068955608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020z9783110704525oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP ROW Ebook Package English 2020z978311069630140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048537525zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de GruyterzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048537525zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789048537525.jpg  a978-3-11-068955-6 Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-069629-5 DG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2b2